{
  "texts": [
    "The second theme that emerges from the green cluster, which includes some terms such as \"mathematics teaching\", \"technology in mathematics\",, \"pre-service teachers\", \"teacher training\", \" TPACK\", \"modelling\",, \"simulation\", \"drawing\", \"diagram\", \"proof\", \"flipped learning\", \"mathematical reasoning\", \"technology acceptance model\", \"3D printing\", \"creativity\", \"augmented reality\", \"architecture\", and \"information and communication\".",
    "This theme emphasizes the investigation of the impact of GeoGebra in mathematics teaching, focusing on areas such as technology integration, teacher training and the design of innovative learning environments.",
    "Researchers explore how GeoGebra, as a dynamic mathematics software package, can be integrated effectively in mathematics education to enhance teaching and learning practices.",
    "Research also indicates GeoGebra positively impacts teachers' instructional practices.",
    "Studies by Bu et al. (2013), Hutkemri and Nordin (2011), Doruk et al. (2013), and Zengin (2017) found that both pre-service and in-service educators viewed GeoGebra as an effective tool for explaining concepts and overcoming difficulties in ways traditional lessons cannot."
  ]
}